solutions.content:
Nice one I took my time to polish a bit and I had fun thinking about how to optimise reducing the amount of conditions/states we would have to consider.

To solve it, first of all let's get equipped with a few variables:
* `res` will store the value of the maximum mountain found so far;
* `curr` is the value of the ongoing mountain length;
* `len` is the length of the initial input;
* `isMountain` and `isDescending` are 2 booleans to store the state, precisely in the guise their name implies.

We will then start looping from index `i == 1` across the whole vector and:
* if we are descending we will:
	* check if we need to reset our range - if either `isDescending` was `true` or `isMountain` was `false` and, in that case, we:
		* set `isDescending` to `false`;
		* set `isMountain` to `true`;
		* reset `curr` to `1` (note: not to `0`, since we count both extremes of the range in its length);
	* in any case, we increment `curr` by one step;
* if we are in a mountain already and only in that case, we will:
	* if we are descending we will:
		* flag `isDescending` as `true`;
		* update `res` to be the maximum between its current value and the incremented value of `curr`;
	* if instead we reached a plataue, we reset `isMountain` (which in turn will trigger other variables resetting as soon as we start ascending again and only in that case).

Once we are done, we can return `res` :)

The code:

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int longestMountain(vector<int>& arr) {
        // support variables
        int res = 0, curr = 0, len = arr.size();
        bool isMountain = false, isDescending = false;
        for (int i = 1; i < len; i++) {
            // checking if we are climbing
            if (arr[i] > arr[i - 1]) {
                // reset conditions: either we were descending or we were
                // not yet in a mountain
                if (isDescending || !isMountain) {
                    isDescending = false;
                    isMountain = true;
                    curr = 1;
                }
                curr++;
            }
            // checking if we are already in a mountain
            else if (isMountain) {
                // if we start descending
                if  (arr[i] < arr[i - 1]) {
                    isDescending = true;
                    res = max(++curr, res);
                }
                // if we reach a plateau
                else if (arr[i] == arr[i - 1]) isMountain = false;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

