# Intuition
so the intution is  we have to form a mountain(which means that it should be a subarray which is strictly increasing and then strictly decreasing).

# Approach
we make variables like -->
. res--> stores the result to be return 

. answer--> temporary answer(which is temporay mountain length).

. wasInc--> when we are goin down the hill it helps us to know that had we gone up_hill in this contiguous subarray. if we are on the down_hill side , we will update our res only if wasInc==true.

. wasIncAndNowDcr--> help us when we are on the up_hill side , this tells that if we are comming from the down_hill side or not...if we are coming from the down hill side then we will have to do a fresh start in search of mountain...else we can continue on the up_hill side as it is as we have not seen down hill side in the contigous subarray

**IMPORTANT**
we have to do a fresh start if we encounter a case where (arr[i]==arr[i-1]) as we have to consider the case of strictly increasing or strictly decreasing..
if you still have any doubts do let me khow in the comment section.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity:O(1)


