let's create 2 dp arrays ,
one for counting length of mountain up from the left side,
the other same purpose from the right side.
Codes are a little too much , but this is a very easy way to come up during interview.
```
class Solution {
    public int longestMountain(int[] A) {
        int result = 0;
        int n = A.length;//n stands for array length

        if(n>0){

         int[] left = new int[n];
         int[] right = new int[n];
         left[0]=0;
         right[n-1]=0;

         for(int i = 1;i<n;i++){
            if(A[i]>A[i-1]){
                left[i]=left[i-1]+1;
            }else{
                left[i]=0;
            }
         }

         for(int j = n-2;j>-1;j--){
            if(A[j]>A[j+1]){
                right[j]=right[j+1]+1;
            }else{
                right[j]=0;
            }
         }


         for(int k = 0;k<n;k++){
          if(left[k]>0 && right[k]>0){
            result = Math.max(result,left[k]+right[k]+1);      
          }   
         }

        }
        return result;
    }
}
```

