solutions.content:
Let each index `k` be the candidate "peak" of the mountain.  Let `i` be the index used to traverse the left-downslope of the mountain and let `j` be the index used to traverse the right-downslope of the mountain.  If both `i` and `j` are able to go downwards starting from the peak `k`, then a mountain has been found.  Return the longest mountain from `i..j` inclusive as the `best` answer.

---

**Runtime:** O(N<sup>2</sup>)

---

*Kotlin*
```
class Solution {
    fun longestMountain(A: IntArray): Int {
        var best = 0
        var N = A.size
        for (k in 1 until N - 1) {
            var i = k
            var j = k
            while (0 <= i - 1 && A[i - 1] < A[i]) --i;
            while (j + 1 < N  && A[j] > A[j + 1]) ++j;
            if (i < k && k < j)
                best = Math.max(best, j - i + 1)  // +1 for i..j inclusive
        }
        return best
    }
}
```

