A simple solution to keep track of rising and going down with a boolean flag and solving it using in one single pass
There are three scenarios which can happen when we are traversing the array

```

public int longestMountain(int[] arr) {
	int max = 0;

	int increaseStart = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
	boolean increase = false;

	for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
		if (arr[i] >= arr[i - 1] && !increase) { //Mountain has started to ascend. Hence we need to mark the mountain start with variables increaseStart.
			increaseStart = i - 1;
			increase = true;
		}
		if (arr[i] == arr[i - 1]) {
			increaseStart = Integer.MAX_VALUE;//If the mountain remains flat then ignore the previous mountain start, as by definition it has to be strictly increasing.
			increase = false;
		}

		if (arr[i] < arr[i - 1]) {
			increase = false; //The mountain is decending hence continously mark our mountain length and check with our max.
			max = Math.max(max, i - increaseStart + 1);
		}
	}

	return max;
}
